trend_summary: Across the series, the landscape stays farmland-dominated, yet the single town in the south slowly radiates new suburbs and light-industrial strips along the highway. Fields consolidate into larger blocks, while wooded cover increases on northern slopes and along riparian corridors. Shoreline recreation structures appear, but overall built-up density remains low.
notable_changes: Gradual outward growth of the southern urban core, forming new residential fringes.
